sentences: Mr. B. (born Mark Lincoln Braun, 1957), is an American boogie-woogie pianist.
Released on 3 September 1996 - Mr. B meets the Bird of Paradise Orchestra.
Mr. B Live at the Kerrytown Concert House 2002
Both Braun and Seeley performed at The Bloomington Blues & Boogie Woogie Piano Festival, in Bloomington, Indiana, in 2017.
Mr. B hauling his piano across Michigan by bike, stopping at Summer Festival, AnnArbor.com, July 10, 2010.
After completing three years towards a Bachelor of Arts in History degree, Braun decided to drop out and pursue a career in blues and boogie woogie style piano.
Every year he brings his bike transported up right piano and plays songs on the University of Michigan campus.
Until recently his only partner in this act was Bob Seeley.
